== Structure == According to the [[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]] and the '''Shoryoshiki''' (諸陵式), the tomb site is recorded to measure "East-West five chō<ref group="脚注">Approximately 545 meters</ref>, North-South four chō<ref group="脚注">Approximately 436 meters</ref>, with two smoke guards."<ref name="shishikoko193">奈良市史 考古編, p.193</ref> Later measurements in the 8th edition of {{ill|Nara City Archaeological Report|ja|奈良市報告|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara City Archaeological Report|qq=}} show smaller dimensions of "East-West 1 chō, 1 bu, 2 rin<ref group="脚注">Approximately 109 meters</ref>, and North-South 38 ken, 1 bu, 7 rin<ref group="脚注">Approximately 69 meters</ref>."<ref name="shishikoko193"/> Its shape is slightly oval, enclosed by rectangular earthen walls, and surrounded by dense matsu and broad-leaved trees, giving it the appearance of a rectangular mound from afar.<ref name="shishikoko193"/> The '''Ryoho Yoran''' (陵墓要覧) classifies it as a round tumulus.<ref name="kadokawa1113"/>
